  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preparedness and Early Response to Public Health Emergencies in Konso and South Omo, Ethiopia.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will work on prediction, prevention, detection and response to health emergencies in the target areas. The project will strengthen the capacity of health institutions and communities to get prepared and respond to public health emergencies and disasters. 
Develop disease surveillance, reporting SOPs and health-met data management system
Activate Rapid Response Team (RRT) for data analysis, interpretation and referrals
Provide emergency drugs and other necessary input, including PPE to selected health facilities
Provide capacity building trainings/on job supports to health staffs
Conduct PVCA
Provide capacity building training for the community on how to maintain healthy behaviour
Establish water points in strategic locations</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Up on the completion, the project anticipates the following significant change: 
Improved public health surveillance and health-meteorology system, Health institution&#x2019;s structures become functional to respond to and anticipate health hazards and Improved Healthy behaviour among the communities on how to maintain a healthy environment to prevent communicable diseases.</narrative>
  </description>
